physical_examinations.vital_signs: Oxygen saturation decreased from 90% to 50% initially. After ventilation support changes, peripheral oxygen saturation maintained at 93-95%.
physical_examinations.relevant_findings: Continuous machine-like murmurs and hepatomegaly. Cyanosis and labored breathing improved under invasive ventilation but could not maintain normal oxygen saturation initially. The patient showed improvement in oxygen saturation after changing to auxiliary ventilation.
physical_examinations.changes_over_time: Initial respiratory distress with low oxygen saturation improved with intervention, indicating a change from severe respiratory distress to a more stabilized state post-ventilation adjustment.
